{{distinguish|Muhammad al-Amin al-Shinqiti}} '''Ahmad ibn al-Amin al-Shinqiti''' (1872–1913) is one of [[Mauritania]]'s most famous [[writer]]s. He is the author of the geographical, literary and historical compendium ''Al-Wasit fi tarájim udaba al-Shinqit'', ed. Fuad Sayyid, Cairo 1958. The survey is the only major Arabic-language work about [[Mauritania]] published by a Mauritanian author.
==Bibliography== *Chouki El Hamel, "The Transmission of Islamic Knowledge in Moorish Society from the Rise of the Almoravids to the 19th Century", ''Journal of Religion in Africa'', Vol. 29, Fasc. 1 (Feb., 1999), pp.&nbsp;62–87
